)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":39,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":48,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Hellena de Allerston was born in 1176, in Pickering, Yorkshire, England, her father, Alan de Alveston, was 37 and her mother, Alice le Despencer, was 22. She married Hugh de Hastings in 1194. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She lived in Fillongley, Warwickshire, England in 1190. She died in 1231, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1176–1231":"1176–1231","1183–Female":"1183–Surnud","1174–1208":"1174–1208","–Male":"Surnud","1200–1246":"1200–1246","1140–1189":"1140–1189","1155–1218":"1155–1218","from 1190 to 1193":"1190 kuni 1193","1176":"1176","1231":"1231","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1183":"1183","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","about 1218":"umbes 1218","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","about 1189":"umbes 1189","about 1200":"umbes 1200","Abt 1180":"umbes 1180","1208":"1208","about 1175":"umbes 1175","1218":"1218","Pickering, Yorkshire, England":"Pickering, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gissing, Norfolk, England":"Gissing, Norfolk, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Allerston, Yorkshire, England":"